step 2:Creating bar charts

 

After loading the data when we move to the analysis section we will see the empty sheet . so we should click the edit button to add data to the sheet and make analysis  and the sheet will be in the edit mode and we can see the fields ,chart types and master items. 





Here we can give appropriate name and description under the properties pane to the sheet 


Then click charts and drag and drop the bar chart

click fields and use zip codes (use text() function to change to string  because it aggregate the zip codes if left as number) and arrest as dimensions by clicking dimension on the chart.


Likewise use Count(ID) for measure in the expression pane


Then click apply and we will get the chart displayed



Now let us change the style of the chart to stacked to see both the false and true arrest for each zip codes.

Go to appearance then  click presentation


In order to show to ten zip codes by number of crimes we have to sort the data. go to sort and under the text(zip code) choose by expression and write count(Arrest) in the expression and choose descending

To show only  top ten we should limit the data and to do that click the chart and click the dimension then under limitation choose fixed number from the drop down list and select top and 10 (the default)

Then unchecked Show others button

Now let us make some color formatting

Go to the appearance and select  colors and legends

 then turn off the auto coloring and choose expression and write the following expression in the expression: if (Arrest='false',Magenta(),DarkGray())

here write the foot note as the DarkGray color is for true arrest and the majenta is for False arrest


Finally click Done and see how the chart look like.then the chart looks like:


Now to show the ten lowest zip codes by crime, copy and paste the chart.

Then change the sorting to descending  and from the limitation section click top and leave 10 as it is and change the chart title 


now clink done and see the top 10 bad and good zip codes


Now drag and drop primary  type  to see the changes in each zip codes



So, one can see the top and least crime zip codes by crime type from the above bar charts.
